{"serial": "07009", "department_serial": 5, "code": "CC0208", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Beauty of Physics", "ch": "物理之美"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": "每堂課皆有評量、請假需依照學校規定"}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chu, Ching-Chi"], "ch": ["朱慶琪"]}, "credits": 2, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "O", "room": "214"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "總教學中心", "en": "Teaching Center"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 20, "selected": 45, "remark": {"ch": "每堂課皆有評量、請假需依照學校規定", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "一、教學目標：\n了解物理學認識世界的方式、學習物理探究的流程、提升推理及批判思考能力。", "en": "“First, the teaching objectives:\nThe course through the demonstration and simulation, to enable students to understand the basic physics concepts, as well as connection between everyday life and the physical phenomenon of. For the introduction of physical concepts, will be the image presentation on the laws of physics, try not to use formula. Daily life there are many phenomena can be understood by the very simple laws of physics, but in modern science and technology under the packaging, often make people think that the physical is very complex. Through the course, students will understand many phenomena from the simple fact of physics, but also through the practice of repeated criticism of the exercise, which enjoy the beauty of the place.“"}, "outline": {"ch": "1.課程綜合介紹、分組、物理基本概念介紹\n2.期初施測(科學推理、量化推理、批判思考等)\n3.費米問題、尺度與系統\n4.物理探究是甚麼？\n5.科學繪圖、溝通與表達\n6.機率、薪資結構與波茲曼分布\n7.建模的練習\n8.?學的探究與實作主題I\n9.?學的探究與實作主題II\n10.熱的探究與實作主題I\n11.熱的探究與實作主題II\n12.電磁的探究與實作主題I\n13.電磁的探究與實作主題II\n14.光的探究與實作主題I\n15.光的探究與實作主題II\n16.Gussimation，估算能力的訓練及養成\n17.期末評量及科學推理、量化推理、批判思考問卷施測\n18.期末總整及回饋", "en": "1. Introduction, introduces the physical concepts and architecture\n2. Our world\n3. Motion I (kinematics)\n4. Motion II (kinematics)\n5. Static I (mechanics)\n6. Static II (Mechanics)\n7. Cycle I (periodic motion, fluctuation)\n8. Cycle II (periodic motion, fluctuation)\n9. Thermal science\n10. Optical, interim progress report\n11. Superstition and Physics\n12. Electromagnetic\n13. Electromagnetic II\n14. Scale Physics\n15. Envelope Physics for School (Important for Estimation)\n16. Invisible physical phenomena\n17. Final Report I\n18. Final Report II“"}, "textbook": {"ch": "Bibliography\n1. “Physics and Technology for Future Presidents“, Richard Muller, Princeton.\n2. “Great Ideas In Physics“, Alan Lightman, McGraw Hill.\n3. “How to help the planet ─ the amount of weight to make the most beautiful scientific experiments,“ Chris, owl study.\n4. “Physical beauty“, Richard. Feynman, the world culture.\n5. “concept of physical“ world culture.“\n參考書目\nBenson, H. (2008). University physics. John Wiley ＆ Sons.\nWolfson, R. (2009). Essential University (Physics Volume 2) (Vol. 2). Pearson Education India.\nYoung, H. D., Freedman, R. A., Sandin, T. R., ＆ Ford, A. L. (1996). University physics (Vol. 9). New York: Addison-Wesley.", "en": "Bibliography\n1. “Physics and Technology for Future Presidents“, Richard Muller, Princeton.\n2. “Great Ideas In Physics“, Alan Lightman, McGraw Hill.\n3. “How to help the planet ─ the amount of weight to make the most beautiful scientific experiments,“ Chris, owl study.\n4. “Physical beauty“, Richard. Feynman, the world culture.\n5. “concept of physical“ world culture.“\n\nBenson, H. (2008). University physics. John Wiley ＆ Sons.\nWolfson, R. (2009). Essential University (Physics Volume 2) (Vol. 2). Pearson Education India.\nYoung, H. D., Freedman, R. A., Sandin, T. R., ＆ Ford, A. L. (1996). University physics (Vol. 9). New York: Addison-Wesley."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100", "en": "100"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討\n實習/實驗\n\n其他", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar", "Practical Training Lab", "", "Others"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "實作相關評量(80％)+期初期末問卷及評量(20％)", "en": "Assessment of Inquiry Prac